{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "VideoObject",
  "name": "VIDEO_TITLE",
  "description": "Detailed description of what the video is about and what viewers will learn",
  "thumbnailUrl": "https://www.yourwebsite.com/video-thumbnail.jpg",
  "uploadDate": "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS+00:00",
  "duration": "PT5M30S",
  "contentUrl": "https://www.yourwebsite.com/video.mp4",
  "embedUrl": "https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIDEO_ID",
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "YOUR_CHANNEL_OR_COMPANY_NAME",
    "logo": {
      "@type": "ImageObject",
      "url": "https://www.yourwebsite.com/logo.png",
      "width": 600,
      "height": 60
    }
  },
  "interactionStatistic": {
    "@type": "InteractionCounter",
    "interactionType": { "@type": "WatchAction" },
    "userInteractionCount": 1234
  },
  "expires": "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS+00:00"
}

<!-- 
INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Replace all placeholder values with actual video information
2. Thumbnail should be high-quality (minimum 160x90, recommended 1920x1080)
3. Use ISO 8601 format for dates and duration
4. Include either contentUrl (direct video file) or embedUrl (embed player)
5. Duration must match the actual video length

REQUIRED FIELDS:
- @context, @type, name, description, thumbnailUrl, uploadDate

RECOMMENDED FIELDS:
- duration, contentUrl OR embedUrl, publisher

OPTIONAL BUT VALUABLE:
- interactionStatistic (views), expires (for time-sensitive content)

DURATION FORMAT (ISO 8601):
- PT5M30S = 5 minutes 30 seconds
- PT1H = 1 hour
- PT45S = 45 seconds
- PT2H15M30S = 2 hours 15 minutes 30 seconds

Format: PT[hours]H[minutes]M[seconds]S

PLATFORM-SPECIFIC EMBED URLS:

YouTube:
"embedUrl": "https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIDEO_ID"

Vimeo:
"embedUrl": "https://player.vimeo.com/video/VIDEO_ID"

Self-hosted:
"contentUrl": "https://www.yourwebsite.com/videos/video.mp4"

THUMBNAIL REQUIREMENTS:
- Minimum size: 160x90 pixels
- Maximum size: 1920x1080 pixels
- Recommended: 1280x720 or 1920x1080
- Formats: JPG, PNG, or WebP
- Use clear, high-quality images

ADDITIONAL PROPERTIES:

For live broadcasts:
"publication": {
  "@type": "BroadcastEvent",
  "isLiveBroadcast": true,
  "startDate": "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS+00:00",
  "endDate": "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS+00:00"
}

For video series/episodes:
"partOfSeries": {
  "@type": "VideoObjectSeries",
  "name": "Series Name"
},
"episodeNumber": 1,
"seasonNumber": 1

For educational videos:
"educationalUse": "Learning about AI optimization",
"learningResourceType": "Tutorial"

For videos requiring subscription:
"requiresSubscription": true,
"isAccessibleForFree": false

INTERACTION STATISTICS:

View count:
"interactionStatistic": {
  "@type": "InteractionCounter",
  "interactionType": { "@type": "WatchAction" },
  "userInteractionCount": 5000
}

Likes:
"interactionStatistic": {
  "@type": "InteractionCounter",
  "interactionType": { "@type": "LikeAction" },
  "userInteractionCount": 450
}

Can include multiple interaction statistics in an array.

REGIONS/COUNTRIES:

Specify where video is available:
"regionsAllowed": "US,CA,GB,AU"

VIDEO QUALITY:

Include quality information:
"videoQuality": "HD",
"videoFrameSize": "1920x1080"

BEST PRACTICES:
- Always include accurate duration
- Use high-quality thumbnails
- Write descriptive titles and descriptions
- Include keywords naturally
- Upload to YouTube/Vimeo for wider reach
- Test embed codes before publishing
- Update view counts periodically
- Add captions/transcripts when possible

RICH RESULTS:
Video schema can appear as:
- Video carousels in search results
- Video previews with thumbnails
- AI platform video recommendations
- Voice search video suggestions
- Featured video snippets
-->
